\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 consumes more and type 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 consumes less; the consumption difference is: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
c_{tb}^{*}-c_{ta}^{*}=\frac{\tilde{\mu}_{ta}-\tilde{\mu}_{tb}}{-u''}.\label{eq:Difference in c}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

These consumption differences cause both transfers across types and efficiency
 losses.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Risk perceptions affect risky consumption, and risky consumption causes
 externalities, so the heterogeneous misperceptions cause transfers across
 groups.
 The net transfer from type 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 to type 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 from heterogeneous instead of homogeneous misperceptions is
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\underbrace{\frac{\tilde{\mu}_{ta}-\tilde{\mu}_{tb}}{-u''}}_{\text{consumption difference }}\cdot\underbrace{\phi_{t}}_{\text{externality}}.\label{eq:Transfer}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

If 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi_{t}>0$
\end_inset

, i.e.
 the positive pecuniary externality from risky consumption outweighs the
 negative contagion externality, then heterogeneous misperceptions cause
 a net transfer from type 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 to type 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

.
 Intuitively, we would say that Republicans are doing more to keep the economy
 going.
 On the other hand, if 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi_{t}<0$
\end_inset

, i.e.
 the negative contagion externality outweighs the positive pecuniary externality
, then heterogeneous misperceptions cause a net transfer from type 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 to type 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

.
 Intuitively, we would say that Democrats are doing more to reduce the spread
 of disease.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The efficiency cost in period 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 from heterogeneous instead of homogeneous misperceptions are the two deadweight
 loss triangles around 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{c}_{t}$
\end_inset

, with total area:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\Delta W_{t}=\frac{s_{t}}{2}\cdot\frac{\left(\overbrace{\tilde{\mu}_{ta}-\bar{\tilde{\mu}}_{t}}^{\text{misperception}}\right)^{2}}{\underbrace{-u''}_{\text{slope of private marginal utility}}}.\label{eq:Efficiency Cost}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Intuitively, type 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

